OL,3,CNesbitt has 'revised plan' to plug
OL,4,Chealth pay gap
OL,6,FThe British Medical Association says
OL,7,Fthe recommended six percent pay rise
OL,8,Fneeds to be paid in full.
OL,10,FDr Francis O'Hagan, Chair of the NI
OL,11,FGPs Committee, said: "Record show GPs
OL,12,Fhere are already paid substantially
OL,13,Fless than our counterparts in England.
OL,15,F"I'm delighted you the minister
OL,16,Fmentioned the gap, and I would really
OL,17,Fvalue that we will get to a position
OL,18,Fwhere DDRB (The Review Body on
OL,19,FDoctors' and Dentists' Remuneration)
OL,20,Fwill be paid in full".
